Description: The type of information being curated.

Description: A set of references (e.g., canonical assembled contigs) which defines a common coordinate space for comparing reference-aligned experimental data.
Syntactic sequences that has a role as reference of an annotation.
Further qualification of dataType, which may be used to indicate the state of processing of the data, aggregation of the data, or presence of metadata.
Valid Values: normalized, dataMatrix, raw, processed, metadata, representative

Description: For files of dataSubtype: metadata, a description of the type of metadata in the file.
Valid Values: individual, biospecimen, assay, data dictionary, manifest, protocol

Description: A type of experimental, clinical, or other data. This typically refers to a high-level data type that can be related to an assay type. For example, a file of dataType `genomicVariants` might have an assay value of `whole genome sequencing`.

Description: Indicates milestone the  data is associated with. Currently only required for projects funded by NTAP, GFF, and NFRI. For GFF studies, this is the ‘progress report’ timeline. Example: if submitting data for the 6-month milestone report for NTAP, progressReportNumber=1.  Also if submitting data associated with first milestone, progressReportNumber =1
Brief free-text comments that may also be important to understanding the resource.
A UUID for a Resource from the NF Research Tools Database
Refers to a funding initiative. This annotation is usually handled by the DCC or funder, not the researcher.
Refers to the funding organization for the generated resource. This annotation is handled by the DCC.
Refers to when the resource was created on the platform.
Refers to the user who created the resource on the platform.
Refers to a user who last modified the resource on the platform.
The entity id for the resource automatically assigned by the platform.

Synapse employs an Optimistic Concurrency Control (OCC) scheme to handle concurrent updates. The E-Tag changes every time an entity is updated it is used to detect when a client's current representation of an entity is out-of-date.
The id of the parent resource, i.e. the parent folder on the platform.
The id of the resource from which access control is inherited.
(Versionable entities only) The current version number of the resource.
(Files only) Refers to the id of the file.
(Files only) File size calculated by the platform.
Refers to the type of the resource on the platform, e.g. “file”.
Refers to the class model the data platform uses for representing the resource. This is a low-level field set by the platform and is not a user annotation.
The author of the resource; preferably use an ORCID ID, GitHub profile link, etc., if available and a text name if not.
Link to a license or name of license applicable for the resource.
